      "span_text": "In a recent published Israeli national survey which was the first nationwide survey regarding the practice of defensive medicine performed among representative sample of 877 board certified expert physicians from eight medical disciplines, several steps to decrease the presence of defensive medicine in their everyday work were offered: medical debriefings of exceptional events, greater transparency to the patient, expectations adaptation with patients, diminution of financial considerations when treating a patient, limiting the compensation fees given to settle medical negligence cases, and finally, new legislation that better protects the doctors' rights."
